{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857180151,"sessionID":"ses_286aa4a97ffeWBCaySwByZbLyY","part":{"id":"prt_d795613c3001nc2swaC9a8C1v1","messageID":"msg_d7955f2100016iY3V6E8mOCVWY","sessionID":"ses_286aa4a97ffeWBCaySwByZbLyY","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement a scheduled garbage collection (GC) mechanism for sandbox resources in `pkg/workloadmanager`. This component periodically scans and cleans up expired, idle, or orphaned sandbox instances to reclaim cluster resources and maintain system health. The GC integrates with the existing Lifecycle Manager (AR-006) and Reconciler Controller (AR-007) to provide configurable retention policies, safe cleanup strategies, and comprehensive observability.\n6: \n7: The garbage collector handles three primary cleanup scenarios:\n8: 1. **TTL Expiration**: Sandboxes that have exceeded their `TTLSecondsAfterFinished` or `MaxLifetimeSeconds`\n9: 2. **Idle Timeout**: Sandboxes that have been inactive longer than `IdleTimeoutSeconds`\n10: 3. **Orphaned Resources**: Sandboxes whose owner references are no longer valid\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Scope\n15: \n16: ### In scope\n17: \n18: | Item | Detail |\n19: |------|--------|\n20: | **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/gc` |\n21: | **CRDs managed** | `AgentRuntime`, `CodeInterpreter` (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1) |\n22: | **Core functionality** | Scheduled GC scans, TTL/idle/orphan detection, safe cleanup with dry-run mode |\n23: | **Integration with** | client-go listers (cached reads), Lifecycle Manager (AR-006), Reconciler (AR-007) |\n24: | **Configuration** | Configurable intervals, retention policies, safe-mode dry-run |\n25: | **Observability** | Prometheus metrics, structured logging, audit events |\n26: \n27: ### Out of scope\n28: \n29: - Sandbox lifecycle management (handled in AR-006)\n30: - CRD reconciler logic (handled in AR-007)\n31: - Multi-cluster GC coordination (separate AR)\n32: - External storage cleanup (e.g., S3 buckets, separate AR)\n33: - Webhook validation/mutation\n34: - Helm chart modifications\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## Design\n39: \n40: ### File layout\n41: \n42: | File | Role |\n43: |------|------|\n44: | `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/gc.go` | **NEW** — GarbageCollector controller, main loop and orchestration |\n45: | `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/scanner.go` | **NEW** — Scan logic for detecting expired/idle/orphaned sandboxes |\n46: | `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/cleaner.go` | **NEW** — Cleanup execution with safety checks and dry-run support |\n47: | `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/config.go` | **NEW** — GC configuration types and validation |\n48: | `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/metrics.go` | **NEW** — Prometheus metrics for GC operations |\n49: | `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/selector.go` | **NEW** — Resource selector utilities for filtering sandboxes |\n50: \n51: ### Type definitions\n52: \n53: **`GarbageCollector`** — Main GC controller:\n54: \n55: ```go\n56: // GarbageCollector periodically scans and cleans up sandbox resources.\n57: type GarbageCollector struct {\n58:     // client is the generated typed client for runtime/v1alpha1\n59:     client runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n60:     \n61:     // arLister provides cached read access to AgentRuntimes\n62:     arLister runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister\n63:     \n64:     // ciLister provides cached read access to CodeInterpreters\n65:     ciLister runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterLister\n66:     \n67:     // config holds GC configuration\n68:     config *Config\n69:     \n70:     // scanner detects candidates for cleanup\n71:     scanner *Scanner\n72:     \n73:     // cleaner executes cleanup operations\n74:     cleaner *Cleaner\n75:     \n76:     // metrics records GC operations\n77:     metrics *Metrics\n78:     \n79:     // stopCh signals shutdown\n80:     stopCh chan struct{}\n81:     \n82:     // wg waits for goroutines to finish\n83:     wg sync.WaitGroup\n84: }\n85: ```\n86: \n87: **`Config`** — GC configuration:\n88: \n89: ```go\n90: // Config holds garbage collector configuration.\n91: type Config struct {\n92:     // Interval is the GC scan interval (default: 5m)\n93:     Interval time.Duration\n94:     \n95:     // SafeMode enables dry-run mode where no actual deletions occur\n96:     SafeMode bool\n97:     \n98:     // EnableTTLCleanup enables cleanup based on TTL expiration\n99:     EnableTTLCleanup bool\n100:     \n101:     // EnableIdleCleanup enables cleanup based on idle timeout\n102:     EnableIdleCleanup bool\n103:     \n104:     // EnableOrphanCleanup enables cleanup of orphaned resources\n105:     EnableOrphanCleanup bool\n106:     \n107:     // DefaultTTL is the default TTL for sandboxes without explicit TTL\n108:     DefaultTTL *time.Duration\n109:     \n110:     // MaxSandboxAge is the absolute maximum age for any sandbox\n111:     MaxSandboxAge *time.Duration\n112:     \n113:     // BatchSize limits the number of deletions per GC cycle\n114:     BatchSize int\n115:     \n116:     // Parallelism controls concurrent cleanup goroutines\n117:     Parallelism int\n118: }\n119: ```\n120: \n121: **`Candidate`** — A sandbox candidate for cleanup:\n122: \n123: ```go\n124: // Candidate represents a sandbox identified for cleanup.\n125: type Candidate struct {\n126:     // Type is the workload type\n127:     Type types.WorkloadType\n128:     \n129:     // Namespace is the resource namespace\n130:     Namespace string\n131:     \n132:     // Name is the resource name\n133:     Name string\n134:     \n135:     // UID is the resource UID\n136:     UID string\n137:     \n138:     // Reason indicates why this resource is being cleaned up\n139:     Reason lifecycle.DeletionReason\n140:     \n141:     // ExpiredAt is when the resource expired\n142:     ExpiredAt time.Time\n143:     \n144:     // Details contains additional context\n145:     Details map[string]string\n146: }\n147: ```\n148: \n149: **`ScanResult`** — Result of a GC scan:\n150: \n151: ```go\n152: // ScanResult contains the results of a GC scan.\n153: type ScanResult struct {\n154:     // Candidates is the list of sandboxes identified for cleanup\n155:     Candidates []*Candidate\n156:     \n157:     // ScannedTotal is the total number of sandboxes scanned\n158:     ScannedTotal int\n159:     \n160:     // ExpiredCount is the number of expired sandboxes\n161:     ExpiredCount int\n162:     \n163:     // IdleCount is the number of idle sandboxes\n164:     IdleCount int\n165:     \n166:     // OrphanCount is the number of orphaned sandboxes\n167:     OrphanCount int\n168:     \n169:     // ScanDuration is how long the scan took\n170:     ScanDuration time.Duration\n171:     \n172:     // Timestamp is when the scan occurred\n173:     Timestamp time.Time\n174: }\n175: ```\n176: \n177: ### GC Flow\n178: \n179: ```\n180: Ticker (config.Interval)\n181:   → Run GC Cycle\n182:     1. Scan Phase\n183:        ├── List all AgentRuntimes (cached via lister)\n184:        ├── List all CodeInterpreters (cached via lister)\n185:        ├── Check TTL expiration (completionTime + TTLSecondsAfterFinished)\n186:        ├── Check max lifetime (creationTime + MaxLifetimeSeconds)\n187:        ├── Check idle timeout (lastActivityTime + IdleTimeoutSeconds)\n188:        └── Check orphaned (owner references validation)\n189:     2. Filter Phase\n190:        ├── Apply retention policies\n191:        ├── Respect batch size limits\n192:        └── Sort by expiration time (oldest first)\n193:     3. Cleanup Phase\n194:        ├── If SafeMode: log only (dry-run)\n195:        └── If not SafeMode:\n196:            ├── Parallel deletion with concurrency limit\n197:            ├── Update metrics\n198:            └── Emit audit events\n199:     4. Report Phase\n200:        ├── Record scan metrics\n201:        └── Log summary\n202: ```\n203: \n204: ### Scanner Implementation\n205: \n206: ```go\n207: // Scanner detects sandbox candidates for cleanup.\n208: type Scanner struct {\n209:     arLister runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister\n210:     ciLister runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterLister\n211:     config   *Config\n212: }\n213: \n214: // Scan performs a full scan and returns candidates for cleanup.\n215: func (s *Scanner) Scan(ctx context.Context) (*ScanResult, error) {\n216:     start := time.Now()\n217:     result := &ScanResult{\n218:         Timestamp: time.Now(),\n219:         Candidates: make([]*Candidate, 0),\n220:     }\n221:     \n222:     // Scan AgentRuntimes\n223:     ars, err := s.arLister.List(labels.Everything())\n224:     if err != nil {\n225:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to list AgentRuntimes: %w\", err)\n226:     }\n227:     \n228:     for _, ar := range ars {\n229:         result.ScannedTotal++\n230:         \n231:         if candidate := s.checkAgentRuntime(ar); candidate != nil {\n232:             result.Candidates = append(result.Candidates, candidate)\n233:             \n234:             switch candidate.Reason {\n235:             case lifecycle.DeletionReasonTTLExpired:\n236:                 result.ExpiredCount++\n237:             case lifecycle.DeletionReasonIdleTimeout:\n238:                 result.IdleCount++\n239:             case lifecycle.DeletionReasonMaxLifetime:\n240:                 result.ExpiredCount++\n241:             }\n242:         }\n243:     }\n244:     \n245:     // Scan CodeInterpreters (similar logic)\n246:     // ...\n247:     \n248:     result.ScanDuration = time.Since(start)\n249:     return result, nil\n250: }\n251: \n252: // checkAgentRuntime evaluates a single AgentRuntime for cleanup.\n253: func (s *Scanner) checkAgentRuntime(ar *v1alpha1.AgentRuntime) *Candidate {\n254:     now := time.Now()\n255:     config := lifecycle.ExtractTTLConfigFromAgentRuntime(&ar.Spec)\n256:     \n257:     ttlStatus := lifecycle.CalculateTTLStatus(\n258:         &ar.ObjectMeta.CreationTimestamp,\n259:         ar.Status.CompletionTime,\n260:         ar.Status.LastActivityTime,\n261:         config,\n262:         now,\n263:     )\n264:     \n265:     if ttlStatus.IsExpired {\n266:         return &Candidate{\n267:             Type:      types.WorkloadTypeAgentRuntime,\n268:             Namespace: ar.Namespace,\n269:             Name:      ar.Name,\n270:             UID:       string(ar.UID),\n271:             Reason:    ttlStatus.ExpirationReason,\n272:             ExpiredAt: *ttlStatus.ExpirationTime,\n273:             Details: map[string]string{\n274:                 \"phase\": string(ar.Status.Phase),\n275:             },\n276:         }\n277:     }\n278:     \n279:     return nil\n280: }\n281: ```\n282: \n283: ### Cleaner Implementation\n284: \n285: ```go\n286: // Cleaner executes cleanup operations for GC candidates.\n287: type Cleaner struct {\n288:     client runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n289:     config *Config\n290:     metrics *Metrics\n291: }\n292: \n293: // Cleanup performs cleanup for the given candidates.\n294: func (c *Cleaner) Cleanup(ctx context.Context, candidates []*Candidate) (*CleanupResult, error) {\n295:     result := &CleanupResult{\n296:         Processed: make([]*Candidate, 0),\n297:         Failed:    make([]*CandidateError, 0),\n298:     }\n299:     \n300:     // Limit batch size\n301:     if len(candidates) > c.config.BatchSize {\n302:         candidates = candidates[:c.config.BatchSize]\n303:     }\n304:     \n305:     // Parallel cleanup with semaphore\n306:     sem := make(chan struct{}, c.config.Parallelism)\n307:     var wg sync.WaitGroup\n308:     \n309:     for _, candidate := range candidates {\n310:         wg.Add(1)\n311:         go func(cand *Candidate) {\n312:             defer wg.Done()\n313:             \n314:             sem <- struct{}{}\n315:             defer func() { <-sem }()\n316:             \n317:             if err := c.deleteCandidate(ctx, cand); err != nil {\n318:                 result.Failed = append(result.Failed, &CandidateError{\n319:                     Candidate: cand,\n320:                     Error:     err,\n321:                 })\n322:                 c.metrics.DeletionFailed(string(cand.Type), string(cand.Reason))\n323:             } else {\n324:                 result.Processed = append(result.Processed, cand)\n325:                 c.metrics.Deleted(string(cand.Type), string(cand.Reason))\n326:             }\n327:         }(candidate)\n328:     }\n329:     \n330:     wg.Wait()\n331:     return result, nil\n332: }\n333: \n334: // deleteCandidate deletes a single candidate.\n335: func (c *Cleaner) deleteCandidate(ctx context.Context, candidate *Candidate) error {\n336:     // In safe mode, just log and return\n337:     if c.config.SafeMode {\n338:         klog.V(2).InfoS(\"GC dry-run: would delete sandbox\",\n339:             \"type\", candidate.Type,\n340:             \"namespace\", candidate.Namespace,\n341:             \"name\", candidate.Name,\n342:             \"reason\", candidate.Reason,\n343:         )\n344:         return nil\n345:     }\n346:     \n347:     // Determine grace period based on reason\n348:     var gracePeriod *int64\n349:     if candidate.Reason == lifecycle.DeletionReasonIdleTimeout {\n350:         // Use shorter grace period for idle sandboxes\n351:         gp := int64(10)\n352:         gracePeriod = &gp\n353:     }\n354:     \n355:     // Delete the resource\n356:     var err error\n357:     switch candidate.Type {\n358:     case types.WorkloadTypeAgentRuntime:\n359:         err = c.client.AgentRuntimes(candidate.Namespace).Delete(ctx, candidate.Name, metav1.DeleteOptions{\n360:             GracePeriodSeconds: gracePeriod,\n361:             PropagationPolicy:  ptr.To(metav1.DeletePropagationBackground),\n362:         })\n363:     case types.WorkloadTypeCodeInterpreter:\n364:         err = c.client.CodeInterpreters(candidate.Namespace).Delete(ctx, candidate.Name, metav1.DeleteOptions{\n365:             GracePeriodSeconds: gracePeriod,\n366:             PropagationPolicy:  ptr.To(metav1.DeletePropagationBackground),\n367:         })\n368:     }\n369:     \n370:     if err != nil && !errors.IsNotFound(err) {\n371:         return err\n372:     }\n373:     \n374:     return nil\n375: }\n376: ```\n377: \n378: ### GC Controller Loop\n379: \n380: ```go\n381: // Run starts the garbage collector.\n382: func (gc *GarbageCollector) Run(ctx context.Context) error {\n383:     klog.InfoS(\"Starting garbage collector\", \"interval\", gc.config.Interval)\n384:     \n385:     ticker := time.NewTicker(gc.config.Interval)\n386:     defer ticker.Stop()\n387:     \n388:     // Run initial scan immediately\n389:     gc.runCycle(ctx)\n390:     \n391:     for {\n392:         select {\n393:         case <-ticker.C:\n394:             gc.runCycle(ctx)\n395:         case <-gc.stopCh:\n396:             klog.Info(\"Stopping garbage collector\")\n397:             return nil\n398:         case <-ctx.Done():\n399:             return ctx.Err()\n400:         }\n401:     }\n402: }\n403: \n404: // runCycle executes a single GC cycle.\n405: func (gc *GarbageCollector) runCycle(ctx context.Context) {\n406:     start := time.Now()\n407:     klog.V(2).Info(\"Starting GC cycle\")\n408:     \n409:     // Scan phase\n410:     result, err := gc.scanner.Scan(ctx)\n411:     if err != nil {\n412:         klog.ErrorS(err, \"GC scan failed\")\n413:         gc.metrics.ScanFailed()\n414:         return\n415:     }\n416:     \n417:     gc.metrics.ScanCompleted(result.ScannedTotal, len(result.Candidates), result.ScanDuration)\n418:     \n419:     if len(result.Candidates) == 0 {\n420:         klog.V(2).Info(\"No candidates for cleanup\")\n421:         return\n422:     }\n423:     \n424:     klog.InfoS(\"GC scan completed\",\n425:         \"scanned\", result.ScannedTotal,\n426:         \"candidates\", len(result.Candidates),\n427:         \"expired\", result.ExpiredCount,\n428:         \"idle\", result.IdleCount,\n429:         \"orphan\", result.OrphanCount,\n430:     )\n431:     \n432:     // Cleanup phase\n433:     cleanupResult, err := gc.cleaner.Cleanup(ctx, result.Candidates)\n434:     if err != nil {\n435:         klog.ErrorS(err, \"GC cleanup failed\")\n436:     }\n437:     \n438:     klog.InfoS(\"GC cycle completed\",\n439:         \"processed\", len(cleanupResult.Processed),\n440:         \"failed\", len(cleanupResult.Failed),\n441:         \"duration\", time.Since(start),\n442:     )\n443: }\n444: ```\n445: \n446: ### Metrics\n447: \n448: ```go\n449: var (\n450:     gcScansTotal = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n451:         prometheus.CounterOpts{\n452:             Name: \"agentcube_gc_scans_total\",\n453:             Help: \"Total number of GC scan cycles\",\n454:         },\n455:         []string{\"result\"},\n456:     )\n457:     \n458:     gcScannedTotal = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n459:         prometheus.CounterOpts{\n460:             Name: \"agentcube_gc_scanned_total\",\n461:             Help: \"Total number of sandboxes scanned\",\n462:         },\n463:         []string{\"workload_type\"},\n464:     )\n465:     \n466:     gcCandidatesTotal = prometheus.NewGaugeVec(\n467:         prometheus.GaugeOpts{\n468:             Name: \"agentcube_gc_candidates_total\",\n469:             Help: \"Number of sandboxes identified for cleanup\",\n470:         },\n471:         []string{\"reason\"},\n472:     )\n473:     \n474:     gcDeletedTotal = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n475:         prometheus.CounterOpts{\n476:             Name: \"agentcube_gc_deleted_total\",\n477:             Help: \"Total number of sandboxes deleted by GC\",\n478:         },\n479:         []string{\"workload_type\", \"reason\"},\n480:     )\n481:     \n482:     gcDeletionFailedTotal = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n483:         prometheus.CounterOpts{\n484:             Name: \"agentcube_gc_deletion_failed_total\",\n485:             Help: \"Total number of failed GC deletions\",\n486:         },\n487:         []string{\"workload_type\", \"reason\"},\n488:     )\n489:     \n490:     gcScanDuration = prometheus.NewHistogram(\n491:         prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n492:             Name:    \"agentcube_gc_scan_duration_seconds\",\n493:             Help:    \"GC scan duration in seconds\",\n494:             Buckets: prometheus.DefBuckets,\n495:         },\n496:     )\n497:     \n498:     gcCycleDuration = prometheus.NewHistogram(\n499:         prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n500:             Name:    \"agentcube_gc_cycle_duration_seconds\",\n501:             Help:    \"GC cycle duration in seconds\",\n502:             Buckets: prometheus.DefBuckets,\n503:         },\n504:     )\n505: )\n506: ```\n507: \n508: ### Default Configuration\n509: \n510: | Parameter | Default | Description |\n511: |-----------|---------|-------------|\n512: | `Interval` | 5m | GC scan interval |\n513: | `SafeMode` | false | Dry-run mode (no actual deletions) |\n514: | `EnableTTLCleanup` | true | Enable TTL-based cleanup |\n515: | `EnableIdleCleanup` | true | Enable idle timeout cleanup |\n516: | `EnableOrphanCleanup` | true | Enable orphaned resource cleanup |\n517: | `BatchSize` | 100 | Max deletions per cycle |\n518: | `Parallelism` | 10 | Concurrent deletion workers |\n519: \n520: ### Cleanup Reason Priority\n521: \n522: When a sandbox matches multiple cleanup conditions, the priority is:\n523: \n524: 1. **TTL Expired** (highest priority) — `TTLSecondsAfterFinished` exceeded\n525: 2. **Max Lifetime** — `MaxLifetimeSeconds` exceeded\n526: 3. **Idle Timeout** — `IdleTimeoutSeconds` exceeded\n527: 4. **Orphaned** (lowest priority) — owner reference invalid\n528: \n529: ---\n530: \n531: ## Impact Analysis\n532: \n533: ### Files created/modified\n534: \n535: | File | Lines (est.) | Type |\n536: |------|-------------|------|\n537: | `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/gc.go` | ~200 | New |\n538: | `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/scanner.go` | ~250 | New |\n539: | `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/cleaner.go` | ~180 | New |\n540: | `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/config.go` | ~100 | New |\n541: | `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/metrics.go` | ~120 | New |\n542: | `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/selector.go` | ~80 | New |\n543: \n544: ### Downstream consumers\n545: \n546: | Consumer | Dependency |\n547: |----------|-----------|\n548: | WorkloadManager | GC runs as part of the workload manager |\n549: | Lifecycle Manager (AR-006) | GC uses lifecycle types for TTL calculation |\n550: | Reconciler Controller (AR-007) | GC triggers deletions that reconciler handles |\n551: | Metrics pipeline | Scrapes GC metrics |\n552: \n553: ### Breaking change risk\n554: \n555: - **None for existing APIs**: This is new functionality\n556: - **SafeMode default**: GC starts in safe mode by default in dev environments\n557: - **CRD compatibility**: Uses existing TTL/idle fields from CRD specs\n558: - **Deletion coordination**: GC deletions are handled by existing finalizer logic\n559: \n560: ---\n561: \n562: ## Alternatives Considered\n563: \n564: ### 1. Use Kubernetes TTL controller instead of custom GC\n565: \n566: **Approach**: Rely on the built-in Kubernetes TTL controller for finished resources.\n567: \n568: **Rejected because**: The upstream TTL controller only supports Jobs and has limited flexibility. AgentCube needs custom logic for idle detection, orphan cleanup, and per-workload-type retention policies. A custom GC provides better control over the cleanup process and integrates with our metrics/logging infrastructure.\n569: \n570: ### 2. Event-driven cleanup instead of periodic scanning\n571: \n572: **Approach**: Trigger cleanup based on watch events rather than periodic scans.\n573: \n574: **Rejected because**: Event-driven cleanup cannot handle \"stuck\" resources or detect idle sandboxes (which require time-based evaluation). Periodic scanning provides a reliable fallback and allows batching deletions for efficiency. A hybrid approach (events + periodic scan) adds complexity without significant benefit.\n575: \n576: ### 3. Single GC controller for all resource types\n577: \n578: **Approach**: Extend the GC to handle Pods, Services, and other related resources directly.\n579: \n580: **Rejected because**: This would duplicate the Reconciler's responsibility and create potential conflicts. The GC should only delete CRs (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter), and let the Reconciler handle cascading cleanup of dependent resources through owner references and finalizers.\n581: \n582: ### 4. Implement GC as a CronJob instead of in-process\n583: \n584: **Approach**: Run GC as a separate Kubernetes CronJob rather than an in-process controller.\n585: \n586: **Rejected because**: An in-process controller provides better integration with the WorkloadManager's lifecycle, shared informer caches, and metrics. A CronJob would require separate authentication, lack access to shared caches, and add operational complexity.\n587: \n588: ### 5. No batch size limit (delete all candidates at once)\n589: \n590: **Approach**: Delete all identified candidates in a single cycle without limiting.\n591: \n592: **Rejected because**: Large deletion batches can overwhelm the API server and trigger rate limiting. A configurable batch size with parallelism control provides safer, more predictable cleanup behavior.\n593: \n594: ---\n595: \n596: ## Dependencies\n597: \n598: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n599: |------------|---------|---------|\n600: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Local | Typed client for runtime/v1alpha1 |\n601: | `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.34.1 | Core Kubernetes client |\n602: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | v0.34.1 | K8s API machinery (labels, selectors) |\n603: | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | v1.x | Metrics collection |\n604: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle` | Local | TTL calculation, lifecycle types |\n605: | `pkg/workloadmanager/types` | Local | Workload type definitions |\n606: \n607: ---\n608: \n609: ## Verification\n610: \n611: ```bash\n612: # Unit tests\n613: make test PKG=./pkg/workloadmanager/gc/...\n614: \n615: # Integration tests\n616: go test -v ./pkg/workloadmanager/gc/... -run \"TestGarbageCollector\"\n617: go test -v ./pkg/workloadmanager/gc/... -run \"TestScanner\"\n618: go test -v ./pkg/workloadmanager/gc/... -run \"TestCleaner\"\n619: \n620: # Build verification\n621: go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/gc/...\n622: \n623: # Verify metrics endpoint\n624: curl http://localhost:8080/metrics | grep agentcube_gc\n625: \n626: # Verify race conditions\n627: go test -race ./pkg/workloadmanager/gc/...\n628: ```\n629: \n630: ---\n631: \n632: ## References\n633: \n634: - [AR-006](#ar-006--sandbox-deletion-and-lifecycle-management) — Sandbox Deletion and Lifecycle Management\n635: - [AR-007](#ar-007--k8s-reconciler-controller) — K8s Reconciler Controller\n636: - [client-go library spec](deployment/client-go.md) — Generated client details\n637: - [Kubernetes Garbage Collection](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/architecture/garbage-collection/) — K8s GC concepts\n638: - [TTL Controller](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/controllers/ttlafterfinished/) — K8s TTL controller documentation\n639: \n640: ---\n641: \n642: *AR-008 — Module: pkg/workloadmanager — Language: Go — Size: S*\n\n(End of file - total 642 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement a scheduled garbage collection (GC) mechanism for sandbox resources in `pkg/workloadmanager`. This component periodically scans and cleans up expired, idle, or orphaned sandbox instances to reclaim cluster resources and maintain system health. The GC integrates with the existing Lifecycle Manager (AR-006) and Reconciler Controller (AR-007) to provide configurable retention policies, safe cleanup strategies, and comprehensive observability.\n\nThe garbage collector handles three primary cleanup scenarios:\n1. **TTL Expiration**: Sandboxes that have exceeded their `TTLSecondsAfterFinished` or `MaxLifetimeSeconds`\n2. **Idle Timeout**: Sandboxes that have been inactive longer than `IdleTimeoutSeconds`\n3. **Orphaned Resources**: Sandboxes whose owner references are no longer valid\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/gc` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775857180127,"end":1775857180147}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857180154,"sessionID":"ses_286aa4a97ffeWBCaySwByZbLyY","part":{"id":"prt_d795618fc001l42eawpQ6AUdUe","messageID":"msg_d7955f2100016iY3V6E8mOCVWY","sessionID":"ses_286aa4a97ffeWBCaySwByZbLyY","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n2: \n3: > Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n4: > Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n5: \n6: ## Purpose\n7: \n8: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\n9: It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\n10: session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n11: \n12: ## Tech Stack\n13: \n14: | Layer | Technology |\n15: |-------|-----------|\n16: | Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n17: | Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n18: | HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n19: | Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n20: | Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n21: | Auth | JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview |\n22: | Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n23: | Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ```\n28: Client / SDK / CLI\n29:   → Router (Deployment :8080)\n30:      ↔ Redis/Valkey (session store)\n31:      → WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n32:         ↔ Redis/Valkey\n33:         → K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n34:   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n35:   Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n36:   Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ## Conventions\n40: \n41: - Go packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n42: - Python CLI at `cmd/cli/`, SDK at `sdk-python/`\n43: - JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n44: - K8s resources use `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group\n45: - Normative language: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n\n> Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n> Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\nIt provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\nsession-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n| HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md","time":{"start":1775857180130,"end":1775857180152}}}}
