{"type":"text","timestamp":1775857245364,"sessionID":"ses_286aa4a97ffeWBCaySwByZbLyY","part":{"id":"prt_d7957194f001qUzc7EblPm4Zlu","messageID":"msg_d795708b1001rYD23xa4PqVTCu","sessionID":"ses_286aa4a97ffeWBCaySwByZbLyY","type":"text","text":"Now I have all the context I need. Let me write the proposal.md for AR-009 — Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core. I'll follow the same format as the AR-008 proposal.","time":{"start":1775857245362,"end":1775857245362}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775857371082,"sessionID":"ses_286aa4a97ffeWBCaySwByZbLyY","part":{"id":"prt_d7957cd37001UzqzOrfsiStC6o","messageID":"msg_d795708b1001rYD23xa4PqVTCu","sessionID":"ses_286aa4a97ffeWBCaySwByZbLyY","type":"text","text":" nil","time":{"start":1775857371079,"end":1775857371079}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857371226,"sessionID":"ses_286aa4a97ffeWBCaySwByZbLyY","part":{"id":"prt_d79571cb5001jg3w67w0djK95L","messageID":"msg_d795708b1001rYD23xa4PqVTCu","sessionID":"ses_286aa4a97ffeWBCaySwByZbLyY","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:15","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","content":"# AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the core HTTP reverse proxy functionality in `pkg/router` to route invocation traffic to sandbox pods. The Router serves as the edge gateway for AgentCube, accepting HTTP requests from clients, resolving sessions to sandbox endpoints via the session store, and reverse-proxying traffic to the appropriate sandbox pods. It integrates with the Workload Manager for sandbox creation on cache misses and provides JWT-based request signing for secure sandbox communication.\n\nThe Router handles three primary responsibilities:\n1. **Session Resolution**: Maps incoming requests (via `x-agentcube-session-id` header) to sandbox endpoints using the session store\n2. **Reverse Proxying**: Proxies HTTP/HTTPS traffic to sandbox pods with path normalization, header forwarding, and JWT injection\n3. **Sandbox Creation**: Triggers sandbox creation via Workload Manager when session is not found\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router` |\n| **Binary** | `cmd/router/main.go` |\n| **Core functionality** | HTTP reverse proxy, session resolution, route handling, JWT signing |\n| **Protocols** | HTTP/1.1, HTTP/2 (h2c), WebSocket upgrade support |\n| **Integration with** | Session store (Redis/Valkey), Workload Manager, Kubernetes API (JWT secrets) |\n| **Configuration** | Port, TLS, concurrency limits, timeouts via flags and env vars |\n| **Observability** | Health endpoints (/health/live, /health/ready), Prometheus metrics, structured logging |\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- TLS termination for upstream (sandbox-to-sandbox TLS handled by sandboxes themselves)\n- Rate limiting per client (handled by API gateway layer)\n- Authentication/authorization (relies on upstream validation via JWT)\n- Multi-cluster routing (single cluster scope)\n- Load balancing across multiple sandbox replicas (handled by Kubernetes Services)\n- WebSocket protocol-specific handling beyond proxy passthrough\n\n---\n\n## Design\n\n### File layout\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/router/server.go` | **NEW** — HTTP server setup, Gin engine configuration, route registration |\n| `pkg/router/proxy.go` | **NEW** — Reverse proxy implementation with httputil |\n| `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | **NEW** — Session resolution and sandbox lookup |\n| `pkg/router/jwt.go` | **NEW** — JWT generation and signing (RS256) |\n| `pkg/router/config.go` | **NEW** — Router configuration types and defaults |\n| `pkg/router/handlers.go` | **NEW** — HTTP handler functions for invocations |\n| `pkg/router/middleware.go` | **NEW** — Concurrency limiting and custom middleware |\n| `pkg/router/health.go` | **NEW** — Health check handlers |\n| `pkg/router/metrics.go` | **NEW** — Prometheus metrics for proxy operations |\n| `cmd/router/main.go` | **NEW** — Entry point, flag parsing, server lifecycle |\n\n### Type definitions\n\n**`Server`** — Main router server:\n\n```go\n// Server is the HTTP reverse proxy server for AgentCube.\ntype Server struct {\n    // config holds router configuration\n    config *Config\n    \n    // engine is the Gin HTTP framework instance\n    engine *gin.Engine\n    \n    // httpServer is the underlying HTTP server\n    httpServer *http.Server\n    \n    // sessionManager resolves sessions to sandboxes\n    sessionManager SessionManager\n    \n    // storeClient provides access to session store\n    storeClient store.Store\n    \n    // httpTransport is the shared transport for proxy connections\n    httpTransport *http.Transport\n    \n    // jwtManager handles JWT signing for sandbox requests\n    jwtManager *JWTManager\n}\n```\n\n**`Config`** — Router configuration:\n\n```go\n// Config holds router configuration.\ntype Config struct {\n    // Port is the HTTP server port (default: 8080)\n    Port string\n    \n    // Debug enables debug mode for Gin (default: false)\n    Debug bool\n    \n    // EnableTLS enables TLS termination (default: false)\n    EnableTLS bool\n    \n    // TLSCert is the path to TLS certificate file\n    TLSCert string\n    \n    // TLSKey is the path to TLS private key file\n    TLSKey string\n    \n    // MaxConcurrentRequests limits concurrent requests (default: 1000)\n    MaxConcurrentRequests int\n    \n    // ReadTimeout is the HTTP read timeout (default: 30s)\n    ReadTimeout time.Duration\n    \n    // IdleTimeout is the HTTP idle timeout (default: 90s)\n    IdleTimeout time.Duration\n    \n    // ShutdownTimeout is the graceful shutdown timeout (default: 10s)\n    ShutdownTimeout time.Duration\n}\n```\n\n**`SessionManager`** — Session resolution interface:\n\n```go\n// SessionManager resolves session IDs to sandbox information.\ntype SessionManager interface {\n    // GetSandboxBySession resolves a session to sandbox info.\n    // Creates new sandbox if session not found and header is empty.\n    GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n\n// manager implements SessionManager.\ntype manager struct {\n    storeClient     store.Store\n    workloadMgrAddr string\n    httpClient      *http.Client\n}\n```\n\n**`JWTManager`** — JWT signing:\n\n```go\n// JWTManager handles JWT key generation and token signing.\ntype JWTManager struct {\n    privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n    publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n    clientset  kubernetes.Interface\n}\n\n// GenerateToken creates a signed JWT with custom claims.\nfunc (j *JWTManager) GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)\n```\n\n### Route table\n\n| Method | Path | Middleware | Handler | Description |\n|--------|------|------------|---------|-------------|\n| GET | `/health/live` | — | `handleHealthLive` | Liveness probe |\n| GET | `/health/ready` | — | `handleHealthReady` | Readiness probe |\n| GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | Logger, Recovery, ConcurrencyLimit | `handleAgentInvoke` | Proxy to AgentRuntime |\n| POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | Logger, Recovery, ConcurrencyLimit | `handleAgentInvoke` | Proxy to AgentRuntime |\n| GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | Logger, Recovery, ConcurrencyLimit | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` | Proxy to CodeInterpreter |\n| POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | Logger, Recovery, ConcurrencyLimit | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` | Proxy to CodeInterpreter |\n\n### Proxy Flow\n\n```\nClient Request\n  │\n  ▼\nGin Router\n  │\n  ├──▶ Concurrency Limit Middleware (semaphore)\n  │\n  ▼\nHandler (handleAgentInvoke / handleCodeInterpreterInvoke)\n  │\n  ├──▶ Extract session ID from x-agentcube-session-id header\n  │\n  ▼\nSessionManager.GetSandboxBySession\n  │\n  ├──▶ Session found? ──Yes──▶ Return SandboxInfo\n  │         │\n  │         No\n  │         │\n  │         ▼\n  │    POST to Workload Manager /v1/{kind}\n  │         │\n  │         ▼\n  │    Validate response, build SandboxInfo\n  │\n  ▼\nDetermine upstream URL from EntryPoints\n  │\n  ├──▶ Match path prefix against invocation path\n  ├──▶ Use first entry point if no match\n  ├──▶ Build URL with protocol prefix\n  │\n  ▼\nGenerate JWT (for Sandbox/SandboxClaim kinds)\n  │\n  ▼\nhttputil.ReverseProxy\n  │\n  ├──▶ Set path, host, forwarding headers\n  ├──▶ Inject Authorization: Bearer <JWT>\n  ├──▶ Set X-Forwarded-* headers\n  │\n  ▼\nSandbox Pod\n  │\n  ▼\nResponse (with x-agentcube-session-id header set)\n```\n\n### Session Resolution\n\n```go\n// GetSandboxBySession resolves or creates a sandbox for the session.\nfunc (m *manager) GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    // Try to load from store first\n    if sessionID != \"\" {\n        info, err := m.storeClient.GetSandbox(ctx, sessionID)\n        if err == nil {\n            return info, nil\n        }\n        if !errors.Is(err, store.ErrNotFound) {\n            return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get sandbox from store: %w\", err)\n        }\n        // Not found, will try to create\n    }\n    \n    // Create new sandbox via workload manager\n    endpoint := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/v1/%s\", m.workloadMgrAddr, mapKindToEndpoint(kind))\n    reqBody := CreateSandboxRequest{\n        Kind:      kind,\n        Name:      name,\n        Namespace: namespace,\n    }\n    \n    resp, err := m.postToWorkloadManager(ctx, endpoint, reqBody)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    \n    // Build SandboxInfo from response\n    info := &types.SandboxInfo{\n        SandboxID:   resp.SandboxID,\n        Name:        name,\n        SessionID:   resp.SessionID,\n        EntryPoints: resp.EntryPoints,\n    }\n    \n    return info, nil\n}\n```\n\n### Reverse Proxy Implementation\n\n```go\n// createReverseProxy creates a reverse proxy for the target URL.\nfunc (s *Server) createReverseProxy(targetURL *url.URL, sessionID string) *httputil.ReverseProxy {\n    proxy := httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy(targetURL)\n    proxy.Transport = s.httpTransport\n    \n    originalDirector := proxy.Director\n    proxy.Director = func(req *http.Request) {\n        originalDirector(req)\n        \n        // Normalize path\n        if req.URL.Path != \"\" && !strings.HasPrefix(req.URL.Path, \"/\") {\n            req.URL.Path = \"/\" + req.URL.Path\n        }\n        req.URL.RawPath = \"\"\n        req.Host = targetURL.Host\n        \n        // Set forwarding headers\n        req.Header.Set(\"X-Forwarded-Host\", req.Header.Get(\"X-Forwarded-Host\"))\n        req.Header.Set(\"X-Forwarded-Proto\", getProto(req))\n        req.Header.Set(\"X-Forwarded-For\", appendClientIP(req))\n    }\n    \n    proxy.ModifyResponse = func(resp *http.Response) error {\n        resp.Header.Set(\"x-agentcube-session-id\", sessionID)\n        return nil\n    }\n    \n    proxy.ErrorHandler = func(w http.ResponseWriter, req *http.Request, err error) {\n        s.handleProxyError(w, req, err)\n    }\n    \n    return proxy\n}\n```\n\n### JWT Implementation\n\n```go\n// GenerateToken creates a signed JWT with the given claims.\nfunc (j *JWTManager) GenerateToken(customClaims map[string]interface{}) (string, error) {\n    now := time.Now()\n    \n    claims := jwt.MapClaims{\n        \"exp\": now.Add(jwtExpiration).Unix(),\n        \"iat\": now.Unix(),\n        \"iss\": \"agentcube-router\",\n    }\n    \n    // Merge custom claims\n    for k, v := range customClaims {\n        claims[k] = v\n    }\n    \n    token := jwt.NewWithClaims(jwt.SigningMethodRS256, claims)\n    return token.SignedString(j.privateKey)\n}\n\n// TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret attempts to persist or load JWT keys from K8s secret.\nfunc (j *JWTManager) TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx context.Context) error {\n    if j.clientset == nil {\n        // Try to create in-cluster config\n        config, err := rest.InClusterConfig()\n        if err != nil {\n            klog.Warning(\"Not running in cluster, using ephemeral JWT keys\")\n            return nil\n        }\n        j.clientset, err = kubernetes.NewForConfig(config)\n        if err != nil {\n            return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create k8s client: %w\", err)\n        }\n    }\n    \n    secret := &corev1.Secret{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      IdentitySecretName,\n            Namespace: IdentityNamespace,\n            Labels: map[string]string{\n                \"app\":       \"agentcube\",\n                \"component\": \"router\",\n            },\n        },\n        Type: corev1.SecretTypeOpaque,\n        Data: map[string][]byte{\n            PrivateKeyDataKey: encodePrivateKey(j.privateKey),\n            PublicKeyDataKey:  encodePublicKey(j.publicKey),\n        },\n    }\n    \n    _, err := j.clientset.CoreV1().Secrets(IdentityNamespace).Create(ctx, secret, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n    if err != nil {\n        if !apierrors.IsAlreadyExists(err) {\n            return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create JWT secret: %w\", err)\n        }\n        // Load existing keys\n        existing, err := j.clientset.CoreV1().Secrets(IdentityNamespace).Get(ctx, IdentitySecretName, metav1.GetOptions{})\n        if err != nil {\n            return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get existing JWT secret: %w\", err)\n        }\n        j.privateKey, err = decodePrivateKey(existing.Data[PrivateKeyDataKey])\n        if err != nil {\n            return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to decode private key: %w\", err)\n        }\n    }\n    \n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### Concurrency Middleware\n\n```go\n// concurrencyLimitMiddleware limits concurrent requests using a semaphore.\nfunc (s *Server) concurrencyLimitMiddleware() gin.HandlerFunc {\n    semaphore := make(chan struct{}, s.config.MaxConcurrentRequests)\n    \n    return func(c *gin.Context) {\n        select {\n        case semaphore <- struct{}{}:\n            defer func() { <-semaphore }()\n            c.Next()\n        default:\n            c.JSON(429, gin.H{\n                \"error\": \"server overloaded, please try again later\",\n                \"code\":  \"SERVER_OVERLOADED\",\n            })\n            c.Abort()\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Health Endpoints\n\n```go\n// handleHealthLive returns liveness status.\nfunc (s *Server) handleHealthLive(c *gin.Context) {\n    c.JSON(200, gin.H{\"status\": \"alive\"})\n}\n\n// handleHealthReady returns readiness status.\nfunc (s *Server) handleHealthReady(c *gin.Context) {\n    if s.sessionManager == nil {\n        c.JSON(503, gin.H{\n            \"status\": \"not ready\",\n            \"error\":  \"session manager not available\",\n        })\n        return\n    }\n    c.JSON(200, gin.H{\"status\": \"ready\"})\n}\n```\n\n### Error Mapping\n\n```go\n// handleProxyError maps proxy errors to appropriate HTTP responses.\nfunc (s *Server) handleProxyError(w http.ResponseWriter, req *http.Request, err error) {\n    msg := err.Error()\n    \n    switch {\n    case strings.Contains(msg, \"connection refused\"):\n        w.WriteHeader(502)\n        json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(gin.H{\"error\": \"sandbox unreachable\"})\n    case strings.Contains(msg, \"timeout\"):\n        w.WriteHeader(504)\n        json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(gin.H{\"error\": \"sandbox timeout\"})\n    default:\n        w.WriteHeader(502)\n        json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(gin.H{\"error\": \"sandbox unreachable\"})\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Metrics\n\n```go\nvar (\n    proxyRequestsTotal = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n        prometheus.CounterOpts{\n            Name: \"agentcube_router_proxy_requests_total\",\n            Help: \"Total proxy requests by status and kind\",\n        },\n        []string{\"status\", \"kind\"},\n    )\n    \n    proxyRequestDuration = prometheus.NewHistogramVec(\n        prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n            Name:    \"agentcube_router_proxy_request_duration_seconds\",\n            Help:    \"Proxy request duration in seconds\",\n            Buckets: prometheus.DefBuckets,\n        },\n        []string{\"kind\"},\n    )\n    \n    sessionCreationsTotal = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n        prometheus.CounterOpts{\n            Name: \"agentcube_router_session_creations_total\",\n            Help: \"Total session creations by kind and result\",\n        },\n        []string{\"kind\", \"result\"},\n    )\n    \n    concurrentRequests = prometheus.NewGauge(\n        prometheus.GaugeOpts{\n            Name: \"agentcube_router_concurrent_requests\",\n            Help: \"Current number of concurrent requests\",\n        },\n    )\n)\n```\n\n### Default Configuration\n\n| Parameter | Default | Description |\n|-----------|---------|-------------|\n| `Port` | 8080 | HTTP server port |\n| `Debug` | false | Gin debug mode |\n| `EnableTLS` | false | Enable TLS termination |\n| `MaxConcurrentRequests` | 1000 | Max concurrent proxy requests |\n| `ReadTimeout` | 30s | HTTP read timeout |\n| `IdleTimeout` | 90s | HTTP idle timeout |\n| `ShutdownTimeout` | 10s | Graceful shutdown timeout |\n\n### HTTP Transport Configuration\n\n```go\n&http.Transport{\n    IdleConnTimeout:     0,  // No limit\n    DisableCompression:  false,\n    MaxIdleConnsPerHost: 100,\n}\n\n// HTTP/2 configuration\nhttp2.ConfigureTransports(transport, &http2.Transport{\n    ReadIdleTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n    PingTimeout:     15 * time.Second,\n})\n```\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Files created/modified\n\n| File | Lines (est.) | Type |\n|------|-------------|------|\n| `pkg/router/server.go` | ~180 | New |\n| `pkg/router/proxy.go` | ~200 | New |\n| `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | ~220 | New |\n| `pkg/router/jwt.go` | ~180 | New |\n| `pkg/router/config.go` | ~80 | New |\n| `pkg/router/handlers.go` | ~150 | New |\n| `pkg/router/middleware.go` | ~100 | New |\n| `pkg/router/health.go` | ~60 | New |\n| `pkg/router/metrics.go` | ~100 | New |\n| `cmd/router/main.go` | ~120 | New |\n\n### Downstream consumers\n\n| Consumer | Dependency |\n|----------|-----------|\n| Client SDK | Sends requests to Router endpoints |\n| Workload Manager | Router POSTs to create sandboxes |\n| Session Store | Router reads/writes session data |\n| Kubernetes API | JWT secret management, in-cluster config |\n| Metrics pipeline | Scrapes Router metrics |\n\n### Breaking change risk\n\n- **None for existing APIs**: This is new functionality\n- **Store interface**: Uses existing store.Store interface\n- **Workload Manager API**: Relies on existing /v1/{kind} endpoints\n- **JWT format**: RS256 signed tokens with standard claims\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### 1. Use Envoy/Nginx as reverse proxy instead of custom Go implementation\n\n**Approach**: Deploy Envoy or Nginx as a sidecar or standalone proxy.\n\n**Rejected because**: A custom Go implementation provides tighter integration with AgentCube's session management, JWT signing with Kubernetes secrets, and dynamic sandbox endpoint resolution. External proxies would require complex Lua/WASM plugins or sidecar coordination to achieve the same functionality. The Go implementation also allows better observability through custom metrics and logging.\n\n### 2. Use gRPC instead of HTTP/REST for proxy protocol\n\n**Approach**: Implement gRPC streaming between Router and sandboxes.\n\n**Rejected because**: Sandboxes may expose various protocols (HTTP APIs, WebSocket, etc.). HTTP reverse proxying is more universal and allows direct passthrough of arbitrary HTTP traffic without protocol translation. gRPC would require wrapping all sandbox traffic, which adds complexity.\n\n### 3. Implement Router as part of Workload Manager (single binary)\n\n**Approach**: Combine Router and Workload Manager into a single process.\n\n**Rejected because**: Separation allows independent scaling (Router is edge-facing, Workload Manager is internal), different deployment patterns (Router can be exposed externally), and clearer separation of concerns. The Router handles HTTP proxying while Workload Manager handles orchestration.\n\n### 4. Use Kubernetes Ingress instead of custom Router\n\n**Approach**: Use Kubernetes Ingress with custom annotations for session routing.\n\n**Rejected because**: Ingress controllers lack awareness of AgentCube's session model and cannot perform dynamic endpoint resolution based on the session store. They also cannot generate JWT tokens for sandbox authentication. A custom Router provides the application-level routing logic required.\n\n### 5. Use Service Mesh (Istio/Linkerd) for traffic routing\n\n**Approach**: Delegate routing to a service mesh with custom routing rules.\n\n**Rejected because**: Service meshes add significant operational complexity and require sidecar injection. AgentCube's routing needs (session-based lookup, JWT injection) are application-level concerns better handled by a purpose-built Router. The custom Router is simpler to deploy and operate.\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Local | Session store interface |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Local | SandboxInfo and types |\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.9+ | HTTP framework |\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.x | JWT signing and validation |\n| `golang.org/x/net/http2` | Latest | HTTP/2 support |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes API client |\n| `k8s.io/api` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes API types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | v0.34.1 | K8s API machinery |\n| `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | v1.x | Metrics collection |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.x | Structured logging |\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\n# Unit tests\nmake test PKG=./pkg/router/...\n\n# Integration tests\ngo test -v ./pkg/router/... -run \"TestProxy\"\ngo test -v ./pkg/router/... -run \"TestSessionManager\"\ngo test -v ./pkg/router/... -run \"TestJWTManager\"\n\n# Build verification\ngo build ./pkg/router/...\ngo build ./cmd/router/...\n\n# Run router locally (requires WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env)\nexport WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=http://localhost:8081\nexport AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE=default\n./bin/router -port 8080 -debug\n\n# Health check verification\ncurl http://localhost:8080/health/live\ncurl http://localhost:8080/health/ready\n\n# Verify metrics endpoint\ncurl http://localhost:8080/metrics | grep agentcube_router\n\n# Test proxy endpoint (with session)\ncurl -H \"x-agentcube-session-id: test-session\" \\\n  http://localhost:8080/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/test-runtime/invocations/health\n\n# Verify race conditions\ngo test -race ./pkg/router/...\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [Session Routing Design](session-routing/design.md) — Router design details\n- [Session Routing Specification](session-routing/spec.md) — Functional requirements\n- [client-go library spec](deployment/client-go.md) — Generated client details\n- [AR-005](changes/AR-005/design.md) — Sandbox Creation Handler\n- [AR-006](changes/AR-006/design.md) — Sandbox Deletion and Lifecycle Management\n- [Gin Web Framework](https://gin-gonic.com/) — HTTP framework documentation\n- [JWT RS256](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7518#section-3.3) — JWT RSA signature algorithm\n\n---\n\n*AR-009 — Module: pkg/router — Language: Go — Size: M*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775857371086,"end":1775857371223}}}}
