{"type":"text","timestamp":1775857438989,"sessionID":"ses_286aa4a97ffeWBCaySwByZbLyY","part":{"id":"prt_d79595ce4001ZJxp7N2SkskHDT","messageID":"msg_d79590896001gqS3YMWDcX8Qnn","sessionID":"ses_286aa4a97ffeWBCaySwByZbLyY","type":"text","text":"I've successfully written the `proposal.md` file for AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心. The proposal includes:\n\n**Key Sections:**\n1. **Purpose** — Explains the Router's role as an edge gateway for routing HTTP traffic to sandbox pods\n2. **Scope** — Defines what's in scope (reverse proxy, session resolution, JWT signing) and out of scope (TLS termination, rate limiting, multi-cluster routing)\n3. **Design** — Comprehensive design including:\n   - File layout for `pkg/router/` and `cmd/router/`\n   - Type definitions for `Server`, `Config`, `SessionManager`, `JWTManager`\n   - Route table with all endpoints\n   - Detailed proxy flow diagram\n   - Session resolution implementation\n   - Reverse proxy with `httputil`\n   - JWT RS256 signing with Kubernetes secret persistence\n   - Concurrency limiting middleware\n   - Health endpoints and error mapping\n   - Prometheus metrics\n4. **Impact Analysis** — Files to create (~1,390 estimated lines), downstream consumers, and breaking change risk assessment\n5. **Alternatives Considered** — Analysis of 5 alternatives (Envoy/Nginx, gRPC, single binary, K8s Ingress, Service Mesh) and why they were rejected\n6. **Dependencies** — All required Go modules including Gin, JWT, client-go, Prometheus\n7. **Verification** — Test and build commands\n8. **References** — Links to related design documents and specifications\n\nThe proposal follows the same structure as the existing AR-008 proposal and integrates with the existing AgentCube architecture, particularly the session store (`pkg/store`) and workload manager.","time":{"start":1775857438986,"end":1775857438986}}}
